  m_Name: giant squid
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::FishData
  <fishName>k__BackingField: Giant Squid
  <fishFact>k__BackingField: "For centuries, giant squid were the stuff of pure legend
    \u2014 no living specimen had ever been photographed until 2004. They can grow
    over 12 meters long, with eyes the size of dinner plates (the largest of any
    living animal) to gather light in the pitch-black deep ocean. Their main predator
    is the sperm whale, and the two regularly do battle in the deep \u2014 sperm
    whales are often found with giant sucker-shaped scars to prove it. "
